news.title: Oyo Hotels to file for $1.2 billion IPO next week: Source
news.para: The hotel aggregator is looking to list in India's financial capital of Mumbai and its IPO is tentatively pegged at between $1 billion and $1.2 billion, the source said, adding it will consist of a fresh issue of shares and an offer for sale from existing shareholders.

news.title: Legitimate tax planning not illegal: ITAT
news.para: In the case of Michael E Desa, a US-based non-resident, it upheld in a recent order the set-off of loss arising on sale of shares of a private company against the profits made on sale of property in India.

news.title: Maharashtra: E-registration of first-sale properties likely from October 2
news.para: The e-registration of such projects will start with the Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA)-registered developers with above 50 tenements, followed by the rest of the builders.

news.title: Noida authority recalls order to seal clubhouses in four societies after residents' stir
news.para: The Authority had taken coercive action against 17 societies and clamped down on their clubhouses over the absence of (or non-functional) sewerage treatment plants (STPs). On Wednesday, however, it took back the sealing order issued against four societies.

news.title: Mumbai: Mahalaxmi Developers' directors held in Rs 18 crore cheating case
news.para: ​​In 2013, the Thakkars launched Mahalaxmi Residency project in Karjat and accepted bookings from 142 people for 66 buildings.

news.title: Ghaziabad: 22 builders pulled up over non-registry of flats
news.para: Officials said these 22 builders have, in the past four years, sold about 15,000 flats without getting the registries done, due to which Rs 70 crore is pending as dues.

news.title: Australian regulators closely watching home loan boom: RBA
news.para: Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) Assistant Governor Michelle Bullock said regulators were closely watching bank lending standards and household debt as credit growth outpaced growth in incomes.

news.title: Mumbai: Tribals to get homes on land owned by Force One in Aarey Milk Colony
news.para: Chief Minister Uddhav Thackeray on Tuesday approved the plan to shift the adivasis to the Force One land. The non-adivasi residents will be provided tenements meant for Project Affected Persons (PAPs).

news.title: Spanish housing stock drops after lockdown-driven buying spree
news.para: Madrid and the Mediterranean seaside town Valencia both saw their pool of homes for sale drop by 11%, while in the Andalusian tourism hubs of Seville and Malaga the available stock dropped by 6% and 5% respectively over the same period.

news.title: PMRDA to soon start Hinjewadi-Shivajinagar Metro corridor
news.para: ​“The project will have to be completed in three years and four months from the commencement date,” a PMRDA official said.

news.title: US homebuilding accelerates as firms aim to close supply gap
news.para: Housing projects started last month rose 3.9 percent from July to more than 1.6 million, seasonally adjusted, the Commerce Department reported, which was above analysts' forecasts.

news.title: Bengaluru has 6,000 illegal layouts; Yelahanka tops the list
news.para: Bengaluru North comes second with 900 illegal layouts spread across 1,080 acres, Bengaluru South 778 layouts in 1,907 acres and Anekal has 501 layouts in 643 acres.

news.title: Meerut divisional commissioner seeks fresh details on erring officials in housing scam
news.para: Surendra Singh had sought details on six points and the GDA had started preparing a report, which would eventually be sent to the state government after being vetted by the commissioner.

news.title: Telangana HC stays auction of 11 acres at Puppalaguda
news.para: ​TSIIC has prepared a schedule for the auction of 95 acres, including the 11-acre land parcel located in survey number 301, at Puppalaguda on September 28.

news.title: Tamil Nadu forms special task force for PMAY-Gramin beneficiaries
news.para: ​The state government has constituted a four member special task force (STF) to expedite identification and distribution of land to beneficiaries of the scheme, according to a senior official in the rural development and panchayat raj department.
